11768.text: [11768] heading 'Reset your Apple Account password on your iPhone, iPad, or Apple Vision Pro'

11769.text: [11769] StaticText 'Reset your Apple Account password on your iPhone, iPad, or Apple Vision Pro'

11779.text: [11779] StaticText 'Tap your name > Sign-In & Security > Change Password.'

11780.text: [11780] image 'iPhone showing the Change Password button in Settings' url: https://cdsassets.apple.com/live/7WUAS350/images/apple-account/ios-18-iphone-15-pro-settings-apple-account-sign-in-security-change-password.png

11784.text: [11784] StaticText 'Follow the onscreen instructions to reset your password.'

11786.text: [11786] heading 'Reset your Apple Account password on your Mac'

11787.text: [11787] StaticText 'Reset your Apple Account password on your Mac'

11797.text: [11797] StaticText 'Click [your name] > Sign-In & Security > Change Password.'

11801.text: [11801] StaticText 'Follow the onscreen instructions to reset your password.'

11803.text: [11803] heading 'If you’re trying to sign in on a new Apple device'

11804.text: [11804] StaticText 'If you’re trying to sign in on a new Apple device'

11807.text: [11807] StaticText 'If you’re not signed in to your Apple Account on an Apple device, you can select “Forgot password or don’t have an Apple Account?” during device setup on the Apple Account sign-in screen.'

11810.text: [11810] StaticText 'After setup, you can reset your password in Settings:'

11816.text: [11816] StaticText 'iPhone or iPad: Go to the Settings > Apple Account. Tap “Sign in manually”, and then tap “Forgot password?” and follow the onscreen instructions.'

11820.text: [11820] StaticText 'Mac: Choose Apple menu \uf8ff > System Settings. Click Sign in, then click “Forgot password” and follow the onscreen instructions.'

11822.text: [11822] heading 'If you don’t have a trusted device'

11823.text: [11823] StaticText 'If you don’t have a trusted device'

11825.text: [11825] heading 'Reset your Apple Account password with the Apple Support app on a borrowed device'

11827.text: [11827] StaticText 'Reset your Apple Account password with the Apple Support app on a borrowed device'

11830.text: [11830] StaticText 'If you don’t have an Apple device but have access to your trusted phone number, you can borrow an Apple device from a friend or family member, or use one at an Apple Store.'

11836.text: [11836] StaticText 'Open the Apple Support app on the borrowed Apple device. If you need to download the Apple Support app, '

11837.text: [11837] link 'find the Apple Support app in the App Store' url: https://apps.apple.com/gb/app/apple-store/id1130498044?pt=2003&ct=support.201487&mt=8

11838.text: [11838] StaticText 'find it in the App Store'

11843.text: [11843] StaticText 'Scroll down to Support Tools, then tap Reset Password.'
